The statement reads as follows: Following the labour unrest since Wednesday, 11 May, the Appeals Committee approved by Council on 31 January has finalised its report post the benchmarking exercise yesterday, 17 May after consulting with all relevant stakeholders. The Acting Municipal Manager, Ms Thokozile Zulu will then table the said report to the Mayoral Committee which will later serve in the Council Meeting to the convened by the Speaker. In the meantime, workers are advised to report for duty with immediate effect.